Package us.ihmc.euclid.referenceFrame.interfaces

Interface FixedFrameQuaternionBasics

  • All Superinterfaces:
    us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.Clearable, FixedFrameTuple4DBasics, FrameQuaternionReadOnly, FrameTuple4DReadOnly, us.ihmc.euclid.orientation.interfaces.Orientation3DBasics, us.ihmc.euclid.orientation.interfaces.Orientation3DReadOnly, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple4D.interfaces.QuaternionBasics, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple4D.interfaces.QuaternionReadOnly, ReferenceFrameHolder, us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.Transformable, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple4D.interfaces.Tuple4DBasics, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple4D.interfaces.Tuple4DReadOnly
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    FrameQuaternionBasics
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FrameQuaternion
    public interface FixedFrameQuaternionBasics
extends FrameQuaternionReadOnly, FixedFrameTuple4DBasics, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple4D.interfaces.QuaternionBasics
    Write and read interface for a quaternion expressed in a constant reference frame, i.e. this quaternion is always expressed in the same reference frame.

    In addition to representing a QuaternionBasics, a ReferenceFrame is associated to a FixedFrameQuaternionBasics. This allows, for instance, to enforce, at runtime, that operations on quaternions occur in the same coordinate system. Also, via the method FrameChangeable.changeFrame(ReferenceFrame), one can easily calculates the value of a quaternion in different reference frames.

    Because a FixedFrameQuaternionBasics extends QuaternionBasics, it is compatible with methods only requiring QuaternionBasics. However, these methods do NOT assert that the operation occur in the proper coordinate system. Use this feature carefully and always prefer using methods requiring FixedFrameQuaternionBasics.

      • setRotationVector

        default void setRotationVector​(FrameVector3DReadOnly rotationVector)
        Sets this frame quaternion to the same orientation described by the given rotation vector rotationVector.

        WARNING: a rotation vector is different from a yaw-pitch-roll or Euler angles representation. A rotation vector is equivalent to the axis of an axis-angle that is multiplied by the angle of the same axis-angle.

        Parameters:
        rotationVector - vector the rotation vector used to set this quaternion. Not modified.
        Throws:
        ReferenceFrameMismatchException - if rotationVector is not expressed in the same reference frame as this.

      • setMatchingFrame

        default void setMatchingFrame​(FrameQuaternionReadOnly other)
        Sets this frame quaternion to other.

        If other is expressed in the frame as this, then this method is equivalent to set(FrameQuaternionReadOnly).

        If other is expressed in a different frame than this, then this is set to other and then transformed to be expressed in this.getReferenceFrame().

        Parameters:
        other - the other quaternion to copy the values from. Not modified.

      • setEuler

        default void setEuler​(FrameVector3DReadOnly eulerAngles)
        Sets this frame quaternion to represent the same orientation as the given Euler angles eulerAngles.

        This is equivalent to this.setYawPitchRoll(eulerAngles.getZ(), eulerAngles.getY(), eulerAngles.getX()).

      • interpolate

        default void interpolate​(FrameQuaternionReadOnly qf,
                         double alpha)
        Performs a linear interpolation in SO(3) from this to qf given the percentage alpha.

        The interpolation method used here is often called a Spherical Linear Interpolation or SLERP.

        Parameters:
        qf - the other frame quaternion used for the interpolation. Not modified.
        alpha - the percentage used for the interpolation. A value of 0 will result in not modifying this frame quaternion, while a value of 1 is equivalent to setting this frame quaternion to qf.
        Throws:
        ReferenceFrameMismatchException - if qf is not expressed in the same reference frame as this.

      • interpolate

        Performs a linear interpolation in SO(3) from q0 to qf given the percentage alpha.

        The interpolation method used here is often called a Spherical Linear Interpolation or SLERP.

        qf - the second quaternion used in the interpolation. Not modified.
